metadata.description: Curated plasmid backbone library for expression vector design
metadata.source: Sequences compiled from Addgene, SnapGene, NCBI GenBank, and vendor documentation

backbones.name: pcDNA3.1(+)
backbones.description: Mammalian expression vector with CMV promoter. MCS in forward (+) orientation.

mcs_position.description: Multiple cloning site downstream of CMV promoter

backbones.name: FLAG-HA-pcDNA3.1-
backbones.description: Plasmid FLAG-HA-pcDNA3.1- from Dr. Adam Antebi's lab is published in Dev Cell. 2014 Mar 4. pii: S1534-5807(14)00069-0. doi: 10.1016/j.devcel.2014.01.028.  This plasmid is available through Addgene.

features.name: FLAG(R) epitope tag, followed by an enterokinase cleavage site

backbones.name: pUC19
backbones.description: Plasmid pUC19 from Dr. Joachim Messing's lab is published in Gene. 1983 Dec;26(1):101-6.  This plasmid is available through Addgene.

backbones.name: pET-28a(+)
backbones.description: Bacterial expression vector with T7 promoter and N-terminal His-tag for protein expression in E. coli.

mcs_position.description: Multiple cloning site with N-terminal His-tag option

backbones.name: pEGFP-N1
backbones.description: Mammalian expression vector for C-terminal EGFP fusion proteins.

mcs_position.description: MCS upstream of EGFP for C-terminal fusions

backbones.name: pLKO.1-puro
backbones.description: Lentiviral shRNA expression vector with puromycin selection.

backbones.name: pSpCas9(BB)-2A-Puro (PX459) V2.0
backbones.description: CRISPR/Cas9 mammalian expression vector with sgRNA cloning site and puromycin selection.

mcs_position.description: BbsI cloning site for sgRNA insertion

backbones.name: psPAX2
backbones.description: 2nd generation lentiviral packaging plasmid. Encodes Gag, Pol, Rev, and Tat.

backbones.name: pMD2.G
backbones.description: VSV-G envelope expressing plasmid for pseudotyping lentiviral particles.

backbones.name: pCMV-Sport6
backbones.description: Versatile mammalian expression vector from Invitrogen with CMV promoter and multiple cloning sites.

backbones.name: pcDNA3
backbones.description: Earlier version of pcDNA3.1, mammalian expression vector with CMV promoter.

backbones.name: pAAV-CMV
backbones.description: AAV transfer vector with CMV promoter for gene therapy applications.

backbones.name: pCAG
backbones.description: Strong expression vector using CAG (CMV early enhancer/chicken beta-actin) promoter.

backbones.name: pGEX-4T-1
backbones.description: Bacterial GST fusion expression vector for protein purification.

mcs_position.description: MCS in GST fusion reading frame

backbones.name: pET-21a(+)
backbones.description: T7-based bacterial expression with C-terminal His-tag option.

backbones.name: pBABE-puro
backbones.description: Retroviral expression vector with puromycin selection marker.

backbones.name: pLVX-Puro
backbones.description: Third-generation lentiviral transfer vector with puromycin resistance.

backbones.name: GFP-P2A-CIAR_pLenti_CMV_Puro
backbones.description: Plasmid GFP-P2A-CIAR_pLenti_CMV_Puro from Dr. Dustin Maly's lab contains the insert GFP-P2A-CIAR and is published in Nat Chem Biol. 2016 Nov 21. doi: 10.1038/nchembio.2244.  This plasmid is available through Addgene.

features.name: antigenic peptide corresponding to amino acids 655 to 669 of the HIV envelope protein gp41 (Lutje Hulsik et al., 2013)
the original enhanced GFP (Yang et al., 1996)
Factor Xa recognition and cleavage site

backbones.name: pCMV-HA-MyD88
backbones.description: Plasmid pCMV-HA-MyD88 from Dr. Bruce Beutler's lab contains the insert MyD88 and is published in Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A. 2006 Jul 18. 103(29):10961-6.  This plasmid is available through Addgene.

backbones.name: pET28a-LIC
backbones.description: Plasmid pET28a-LIC from Dr. Cheryl Arrowsmith's lab contains the insert None.  This plasmid is available through Addgene.

backbones.name: pcDNA3.1(-)
backbones.description: Mammalian expression vector with CMV promoter. MCS in reverse (-) orientation relative to f1 origin. Same expression cassette as pcDNA3.1(+).

mcs_position.description: Multiple cloning site downstream of CMV promoter
